ne of us from my guild were hunting in Icewell today killing the dorfs for the armor that a couple of the tanks wanted.  Mainly looking for the legs/breastplate the watchers dropped every blue moon.  As I am sure all of you who hunt there know beggers are always asking for the scrap armor that isnt needed...and tonight was no different.  We gave away the gaunts/boots as they dropped and kept whatever we needed.  <br>
One particular begger was really a pain, sending multiple tells to everyone of us asking for armor.  We let him loot boots and gaunts and then told him anything else would be used by us and the gravy train was over.<br>
Eventually we got lucky and legs dropped for one of our warriors who happened to not be in the kill group.  I locked the corpse for him until enough time had passed and noticed the begger was standing there watching right next to the &quot;rightfull looter&quot;.  <br>
I told the begger in say DONT LOOT THE CORSPE and then told the rightful looter to loot, stood up intending for him to loot.  The begger jumped in and looted the legs, put them on and ran over and zoned.  <br>
I told everyone there to petition that he had ninja'd and zoned as well.  We all petition that he ninja'd and after zoning I told him I was going to report him for ninja looting.  The begger zoned back in and I told the other group in zone via OOC to be careful he was ninja looting.  <br>
(pay attention this will be important later)<br>
The begger said in shout &quot;gee, I feel sorry about looting the legs, I am sorry&quot;<br>
-----TIME PASSES------<br>
Guides start answering our various petitions and we inform them what happened, eventually being escalated to full GM.<br>
The GM tells us that there is nothing he/she/it can do unless we can prove he intended to ninja loot and could we /report anything with proof.  Our cleric scrolls up /reports me saying dont loot and him saying sorry he looted.<br>
I figure that was enough proof..I mean wtf why would we LET him loot legs ?  Why would we say congrats and cheer the rightfull looter if we planned to give to the begger?<br>
---TIME PASSES----<br>
GM responds that he/she/it got the /report and since the begger expressed that he was sorry for looting, obviously he didnt mean to ninja loot and therefor we were SOL and nothing was going to be done.<br>
I start debating with the GM that :<br>
A- the begger was only level 37, could in no way kill the watcher that dropped the legs so couldnt rightfully loot them<br>
B-I told him not to loot, therefor expressing my desire for him to not get the legs<br>
C-he admitted looting them.<br>
D-If it was &quot;accidental&quot; why did he loot and run for zone?<br>
E-Why did he wait for me to stand up and then jump in and loot the watcher<br>
<br>
The GM started repeating &quot;rule 11&quot; and that since he said sorry, in he/she/it's eyes it was an accidental loot and not a ninja loot.  Unless we had hard proof that he &quot;intended&quot; to ninja loot, we were SOL.<br>
<br>
Many of us talked to the gm expressing basically the same thing and all we got was &quot;RULE 11&quot; &quot;RULE 11&quot; cant help you &quot;RULE 11&quot; RULE 11&quot;.<br>
<br>
The Beggers name in case you are wondering is:<br>
***** Xemus 37th warrior, unguilded ******<br>
<br>
Eventually the GM said that the legs would be taken from Xemus and destroyed. Also, that Xmeus would get an officail warning.  I asked why destroyed, why not given to the rightful looter?  no explanation given.<br>
<br>
Once again, I am boggled...if the GM can admit that Xemus shouldnt have the legs, WTF...why not give to the right person who should have gotten the legs?  <br>
<br>
I guess I should just be happy Xemus wont get the damn things, but then, I will never know if the GM was just saying that to get rid of the constant tells from us.<br>
<br>
SO, moral of the story for Ninja looter wanna be's.  just appologize after you loot Yelinak or trak...explain how sorry you feel and you wish you could give the item back...at a minimum you will have screwed over the rightful looter of the item and you might even get to keep it.<br>
<br>
***disclaimer :  I can't type or spell worth a damn &lt;G&gt; ***<br>
