I don't think you can have more proof that the beggar was wrong and that he does in no way deserve the legs, but your warrior does.<br>
I do not know what else the GM can ask for other than all those reports and petitions, even with the beggar_01 admitting it.<br>
<br>
This is sad. Sometimes I think our GM's don't give rats ass about us.<br>
When I hear and see stories from great GMs on other servers, which are fun and nice and good people, and all I see from our GMs is ignorance...<br>
<br>
I got help from GMs usually when I got bugged, when I took 10000HP dmg off a 3 feet fall or so. Just usually took a while. But if you have such issues, they never care at all I think....<br>
And have you ever seen a GM on our server have fun or interact with the players?<br>
I didn't.<br>
<br>
Maybe its Verants Guidelines fault, but I have the impression our GMs and Guides are all day long just busy not to do anything that they could be *beaten up* by Verant - instead of adding some fun for the players in any way.<br>
They have their Guidelines book in front of them and have their prepared *case 329a - do this and that* thingies and just do this and that. Period.<br>
<br>
